# Backend — Core Universe

The backend project lives at the root of this repo: **core-universe** (Rust Core + Python DeAI + ops + tools)

## Structure

- **core/** — Rust blockchain (blockchain, consensus, rpc, staking, ...) and **core/deai/** — Python Worker
- **ops/deploy/** — Deployment, environments, monitoring
- **tools/** — faucet, devtools
- **scripts/** — run-worker, health-check, join-network
- **configs/** — monolith_*.toml, worker configs

## Rust (core/)

- Run commands from **core/**: `cargo build`, `cargo test --workspace`, `cargo clippy --workspace`, `cargo fmt --all`
- Use `core/Cargo.toml` as workspace root; don't move crates out of core/
- Avoid `unsafe` unless necessary; focus on memory safety and performance

## Python (core/deai/)

- Python 3.10+; dependencies from **core/deai/requirements.txt** only
- Config: **worker_config.toml**; override with env (.env from .env.example) — never commit `.env` or `worker_key.json`
- Wallet: supports `AXIONAX_WALLET_PATH`, `WORKER_PRIVATE_KEY`, `WORKER_KEY_PASSWORD`; path can be relative to config
- Run tests: `python -m pytest . -v --tb=short` from core/deai/

## Config & Security

- Secrets go in env or .env; .env.example provides a template
- Run/join docs: see README.md
